n of Maurice Bishop International Airport (GND), Grenada\\u2019s primary gateway for international travel, and Lauriston Airport (CRU), which serves the island of Carriacou. Both airports play a vital role in national connectivity, economic development, and regional integration.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Mission Statement\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"To provide safe, secure, efficient and profitable world-class airport facilities and services, consistent with international standards through a highly skilled and committed workforce in support of the economic development of Grenada.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Vision Statement\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"To be a leader in providing world-class airport facilities and services in the Caribbean.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Objectives\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ul,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"To provide adequate capacity for aircraft, passengers, air cargo, and vehicle movements in a safe environment.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"To provide for and facilitate passenger, operator, and staff convenience.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"To ensure continued financial viability.\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.li,{children:\"To ensure that physical development plans remain flexible to allow for future expansion.\"}),`\n`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Mandate\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:\"The GAA is committed to the advancement of Grenada\\u2019s aviation sector by overseeing the development, modernization, and maintenance of airport facilities. Our primary objectives include:\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Ensuring Safety and Security\"}),\" Implementing and maintaining the highest international standards in aviation security, air traffic management, and operational safety.\",(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Enhancing Efficiency\"}),\" Providing seamless, customer-focused services that optimize passenger experience and operational perfor